  "text": "In vitro experiments commonly use a luciferin reporter system, in primary cells or cell lines, to measure activity of clock genes in real time [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . In addition, the levels of proteins or RNA can be quantified at multiple time-points to further validate and mechanistically address circadian observations. A summary of these different methodologies is depicted in Fig. 2 .",
